LabelBlockProxy
public class EventListProxy
extends TopLevelListProxy

A structured list of event names.

Event lists are used in various places in a module, where several events are grouped together. The most common application is on transitions in graphs (LabelBlockProxy), but event lists can also be used for parameter bindings (ParameterBindingProxy) of instance components or alias declarations (EventAliasProxy).

Technically, an event list is an implementation of the List interface, which can have two different kinds of elements.

IdentifierProxy
Identifiers are used to include a single event with a given name (or all elements of an array of events) in an event list. There can be simple identifiers (SimpleIdentifierProxy) that are just names or indexed identifiers (IndexedIdentifierProxy) that can have one or more array indexes.
ForeachEventProxy
This construct can be used to include several events by processing a loop.

Author:
Robi Malik
